input: {
    "context": "We develop open source projects to stay ahead of the best patterns for building agents. Then, we incorporate these learnings into LangSmith - our commercial agent engineering platform. LangSmith helps companies understand, improve, and ship agents as fast as possible, whether they use our open source frameworks or not.\nThe LangChain story\n-------------------\nLangChain started as Harrison Chase's side project in late 2022. It was a single Python package pushed from a personal GitHub account with no grand plan behind it. Then ChatGPT launched, and everything changed.\nHarrison teamed up with co-founder Ankush Gola to start LangChain, the company, in early 2023, and we've been building ahead of the industry ever since. After LangChain, we launched LangGraph to give developers control over complex agent systems, with a runtime built for production.\nAs we shipped more agents, we saw a gap in tooling for testing and debugging them. We launched LangSmith, an independent commercial platform, for AI observability. We quickly added services for agent evaluation, deployment, and a no-code agent builder. Most recently, we released an agent harness called Deep Agents for autonomous, long-horizon tasks.\nToday, we work with 35% of the Fortune 500, have crossed 1 billion open source downloads, and ingest over 1 billion events per day on LangSmith. We're headquartered in San Francisco, with offices in New York, Boston, and Amsterdam.\nAbout LangChain**\n-------------------\nLangChain is the agent engineering platform powering top engineering teams, from AI startups to global enterprises. Its open-source frameworks, including LangChain, LangGraph, and Deep Agents, have surpassed 1 billion cumulative downloads and are used by over one million practitioners. LangSmith, the observability, evaluation, and deployment platform, serves over 300 enterprise customers and 5 of the Fortune 10. LangChain is backed by Sequoia Capital, Benchmark, and IVP. For more information, visit [**langchain.com**](https://langchain.com/?ref=blog.langchain.com).\n‍\n###\n### Backed by the best in the business\n### In the news\n[\n### Exclusive: Early AI darling LangChain is now a unicorn with a fresh $125 million in funding\nFull story\n\n\n](https://fortune.com/2025/10/20/exclusive-early-ai-darling-langchain-is-now-a-unicorn-with-a-fresh-125-million-in-funding/)\n[\n### Open source agentic startup LangChain hits $1.25B valuation\nFull story\n\n\n](https://techcrunch.com/2025/10/21/open-source-agentic-startup-langchain-hits-1-25b-valuation/)\n[\n### Context Engineering Our Way to Long-Horizon Agents: LangChain’s Harrison Chase\nFull story\n\n\n](https://sequoiacap.com/podcast/context-engineering-our-way-to-long-horizon-agents-langchains-harrison-chase/)",
